Limited case reports of treprostinil use in pregnant women are insufficient to inform a drug-associated risk of adverse developmental outcomes. However, there are risks to the mother and the fetus associated with pulmonary arterial hypertension (see 
                                    Clinical Considerations
                                 ). In animal studies, no adverse reproductive and developmental effects were seen for treprostinil at 39 and 3145 times the human exposure when based on Cmax and AUC, respectively, following a single YUTREPIA dose of 79.5 mcg [see Clinical Pharmacology (12.3)].
